==English==
==== Etymology ====
The nautical sense is simply [[scuttle]] + [[butt]].  The slang sense was originally derived the exchange of gossip that occurs around a scuttlebutt.  Compare [[furphy]].
=== Noun ===
'''scuttle-butt''' (also '''scuttlebutt''')
#A [[butt]] with a [[scuttle]], a [[cask]] with a hole cut in it, for holding drinking water [[aboard]] [[ship]]
#(''Slang'') [[gossip]]

